ger misfeel and misperception by others. One is misread by others and receives confusing internal information. Communication of and to the self is irrevocably damaged. Wachs describes the experience as a social disability. People found a host of creative ways to reinvigorate their sense of self and self-expression. Like so many she interviewed, Wachs experiences a process of change and growth as she is challenged to think more deeply about ableism, identity, and who she wants to be.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aFacial expressionxSocial aspects. 0aFacial paralysisxSocial aspects. 0aParalyticsxSocial conditions. 0aSelf-perception. 0aSocial perception. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  adisability, paralysis, coping with disability, appearance, beauty, identity, health, medicine, synkinesis, ableism, discrimination.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishz978311131909408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023z978311131812708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079130340uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197880535440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978805354423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978805354/original  a978-3-11-079130-3  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131812-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131909-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2